  "response": "Yes, Bernie Sanders is often characterized as a populist. He advocates for policies that aim to address economic inequality and promote social justice. Sanders has long championed views that seek to represent the interests of the common people, especially working-class citizens, against the perceived interests of elites and large corporations. His platform includes proposals for universal healthcare, tuition-free public college, and progressive taxation, all of which are aligned with populist principles.",
